33 "§ 74D-2.1. Criminal background checks.
34 (a) Authorization. – Upon receipt of an application for a license or registration, the Board
35 shall conduct a background investigation to determine whether the applicant meets the
36 requirements for a license or registration as set out in G.S. 74D-2(d). The Department State
37 Bureau of Public Safety Investigation may provide a criminal record check to the Board for a
38 person who has applied for a new or renewal license or registration through the Board. The Board
39 shall provide to the Department of Public Safety, State Bureau of Investigation, along with the
40 request, the fingerprints of a new applicant, and the Department of Public Safety State Bureau of
41 Investigation shall provide a criminal record check based upon the applicant's fingerprints. The
42 Board may request a criminal record check from the Department of Public Safety State Bureau
43 of Investigation for a renewal applicant based upon the applicant's fingerprints in accordance
44 with policy adopted by the Board. The Board shall provide any additional information required
45 by the Department of Public Safety State Bureau of Investigation and a form signed by the
46 applicant consenting to the check of the criminal record and to the use of the fingerprints and
47 other identifying information required by the State or national repositories. The applicant's
48 fingerprints shall be forwarded to the State Bureau of Investigation for a search of the State's
49 criminal history record file, and the State Bureau of Investigation shall forward a set of the
50 fingerprints to the Federal Bureau of Investigation for a national criminal history check. The
51 Department of Public Safety State Bureau of Investigation may charge each applicant a fee to be
