10 "§ 74D-3. Exemptions.
11 The provisions of this Chapter shall not apply to:to the following:
12 (1) A person, firm, association or corporation that sells or manufactures alarm
13 security systems, unless the person, firm, association or corporation makes
14 personal solicitations at a residence or business to advise, design, or consult
15 on specific types and specific locations of alarm security system devices,
16 installs, services, monitors, or responds to alarm security systems at or from a
17 protected premises or a premises to be protected and thereby obtains
18 knowledge of specific application or location of the alarm security system. A
19 person licensed under this Chapter may hire a consultant to troubleshoot a
20 location or installation for a period of time not to exceed 48 hours in a
21 one-month period if the licensee submits a report to the Board within 30 days
22 from the date of the consultation designating the consultant as a temporary
23 consultant;
24 (2) Installation, servicing or responding to fire alarm systems or any alarm device
25 which is installed in a motor vehicle, aircraft or boat;boat.
26 (3) Installation or service of an alarm electronic security system on property
27 owned by or leased to the installer;installer.
28 (4) An alarm monitoring company located in another state which demonstrates to
29 the Board's satisfaction that it does not conduct any business through a
30 personal representative present in this State but which solicits and conducts
31 business solely through interstate communication facilities such as telephone
32 messages, earth satellite relay stations and the United States postal service;
33 and
34 (5) A person or business providing alarm systems services to a State agency or
35 local government if that person or business has been providing those services
36 to the State agency or local government for more than five years prior to the
37 effective date of this Chapter, and the State agency or local government joins
38 with the person or business in requesting the application of this exemption.
39 (6) Installation or service of a locking device that records entry and exit data and
40 does not transmit the data in real time to an on-site or off-site monitoring
41 location, provided the installer is licensed by the North Carolina Locksmith
42 Licensing Board.
43 (7) An entity through which a customer accesses marketing or advertising
44 material or installation instructions for a security system.
45 (b) A person licensed under this Chapter may utilize a consultant or manufacturer's
46 representative to troubleshoot a location or installation if accompanied by the licensee and the
47 licensee submits a report to the Board within 30 days from the date of the consultation designating
48 the consultant as a temporary consultant.
49 "§ 74D-4. Alarm Security Systems Licensing Board.
50 (a) The Alarm Security Systems Licensing Board is hereby established.
